"Curve 1" }}}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 204 "5.  Three-dimensional plots.  Maple can also provide represent
ations for graphs of functions of two variables.  The graphs of such f
unctions are surfaces in three-dimensional space.  The Maple command i
s:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "    \+
 " }{TEXT 270 0 "" }{TEXT 271 4 "plot" }{TEXT 272 2 "3d" }{TEXT -1 2 "
( " }{TEXT 273 4 "expr" }{TEXT -1 2 ", " }{TEXT 274 1 "x" }{TEXT -1 8 
"=range, " }{TEXT 275 0 "" }{TEXT 276 2 "y=" }{TEXT -1 19 "range [, op
tions]);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
6 "where " }{TEXT 277 4 "expr" }{TEXT 281 1 " " }{TEXT -1 24 "is a sym
bolic expression" }{TEXT 279 1 " " }{TEXT -1 48 "which represents the \+
function to be plotted and " }{TEXT 278 1 "x" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }
{TEXT 282 0 "" }{TEXT 283 1 "y" }{TEXT 284 0 "" }{TEXT -1 44 " are the
 two independent variables used in  " }{TEXT 280 4 "expr" }{TEXT -1 
25 "  to define the function." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " }{TEXT 285 0 "" }{TEXT 286 6 "plot3d
" }{TEXT 287 0 "" }{TEXT -1 238 " command will generate a surface plot
 for the function over the rectangular range specfied in the command s
tatement.  The surface plot can be rotated, tipped over and turned aro
und to see the surface plot from all side and all viewpoints." }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 278 "For each
 of the following functions provide a plot which shows the graph.  Cho
ose reasonable values for the ranges of x and y.  Rotate, where approp
riate, to present a good view of the graph.  The last two graphs are i
mplicitly defined functions which require the Maple command " }{TEXT 
297 0 "" }{TEXT 298 15 "implicitplot3d " }{TEXT 299 0 "" }{TEXT -1 29 
"which is part of the package " }{TEXT 300 0 "" }{TEXT 301 5 "plots" }
{TEXT 302 0 "" }{TEXT -1 1 "." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "a.   " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "z" "6#%\"zG" }
